Canonical context is in `AGENTS.md` at the repo root — treat it as authoritative
and read it. This rule is a thin Cursor-specific pointer (tenet: portable, no
editor lock-in). Do not duplicate AGENTS.md content into rules.

Hard rules, always:
- Everything is versioned — commit code, configs, scaffolding, decisions. Nothing
  important lives only in a chat or one machine.
- Cross-platform: Mac + Windows both work out of the box. Prefer Python over shell
  for tooling. No symlinks. Note OS-specific commands when they differ.
- TDD: write tests before implementation. 80%+ coverage on `src/`.
- Secrets only in `.env` (gitignored) / CI secrets — never in code, commits, or logs.
- No firm IP in this public repo. Verify external product/API facts before coding.
- Chandra is senior; be concise, one clear next action, skip basics, flag scope creep.
